==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eriometer
<hw>E`ri*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wool +
<ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>An instrument for
measuring the diameters of minute particles or fibers, from the size of
the colored rings produced by the diffraction of the light in which the
objects are viewed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eriophyllum</ent>⟦br⟧
